<item>
            <title>[JDK-8307926] Support byte-sized atomic bitset operations</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8307926</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8293117&quot; title=&quot;Add atomic bitset functions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8293117&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8293117&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added Atomic bitset operations for int-sized and (if different) pointer-sized values. But there are existing use-cases in HotSpot that need to operate on byte-sized values.  So we need to add support for such.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
