URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://git.openjdk.org/jdk/pull/13952&quot;&gt;https://git.openjdk.org/jdk/pull/13952&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date: 2023-05-12 09:57:44 +0000</comment>
                            <comment id="14581105" author="kbarrett" created="Thu, 11 May 2023 22:20:27 -0700"  >[~dholmes] Many hardware platforms don&amp;#39;t support byte-sized atomic bitops, so yes, we&amp;#39;ll need to do something like we did to support cmpxchg with byte-sized values, e.g. CmpxchgByteUsingInt.  Of course, the default (and currently only) implementation of these operations uses cmpxchg, so accidentally happen to work on byte-sized values already.  But we need to make that &amp;quot;official&amp;quot; and make sure future platform specializations handle it (possibly by continuing to use cmpxchg and CmpxchgByteUsingInt).&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14581085" author="dholmes" created="Thu, 11 May 2023 18:36:56 -0700"  >Does the hardware support byte atomic operations? Otherwise we will need to use the cas-loop trick on the entire word (which will need to be suitably aligned).</comment>
